rawReviews.name: Rosemary Patton
rawReviews.text:
Our front door was in disrepair.  The first visit by Slade was to determine what would be required to repair if possible.  We had thought we might have to purchase a new door.
Slade assessed the damage and knew immediately what had to be done and  advised that he could repair the door using a sanding and painting technique.  He took pictures and later returned with a paint chart so we could select a color.
This was a 3-day process.  He was always on time and called prior to his arrival as we had requested. He was very professional and explained exactly what he was doing at each step of the process.  He was meticulous and took the necessary time to ensure the work was done properly.  Slade stands by his work.
The completed product was outstanding. We intend to ask him to return in the future regarding other projects.
